Ensure WebSocket handlers properly integrate with Supabase storage backend. The epic decision is to keep existing WebSocket (not migrate to Supabase Realtime), but we need to verify WebSocket operations correctly persist to Supabase.

## Context

WebSocket server handles real-time student code updates during live sessions. When students type code:
1. WebSocket receives update from browser
2. Server updates in-memory session state
3. Server persists to storage backend (now Supabase)

Need to ensure this flow works correctly with Supabase repositories and handle any race conditions or transaction requirements.

