## Testing Pattern (Per-Test Mocking)

Create src/server/persistence/supabase/__tests__/user-repository.test.ts

**Use per-test-file Jest mocking** (cleaner than global setupTests):

```typescript
// Mock Supabase client at top of test file
const mockFrom = jest.fn();
const mockSelect = jest.fn();
// ... other mock functions

jest.mock('../../../supabase/client', () => ({
  getSupabaseClient: jest.fn(() => ({
    from: mockFrom,
  })),
}));

beforeEach(() => {
  jest.clearAllMocks();

  // Set up default mock chain
  mockFrom.mockImplementation(() => ({
    select: mockSelect.mockReturnValue({
      eq: mockEq.mockReturnValue({ single: mockSingle }),
    }),
    // ... other chains
  }));
});

// Override mockFrom per-test when needed
it('specific test', () => {
  mockFrom.mockReturnValue({
    select: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({ data: mockData, error: null })
  });
});
```

**Key advantages:**
- Each test file controls its own mocks (no shared state)
- Override mockFrom per-test for special cases (like queries that await directly)
- More explicit and standard Jest pattern
